						<summary>

						<p>Two pieces of a broken slab lying in the Gaṇgamma shrine</p>						

						<p>1540 A.D.</p>						

						<p>This registers a gift of eight <hi rend="italic">koḷaga</hi> of land to Mācha Ma[luga], son of Golapāpa by <hi rend="italic">mahāmaṇḍalēśvara</hi> Timmarāja, son of Viruparāja, for supplying water in the water-shed maintained by him at the fair <hi rend="italic">(saṅte)</hi> in Kadiri. The gift land was situated in Chemmūru which belonged to the <hi rend="italic">nāyakatana</hi> of the donor.</p>						

						<p>It is dated <hi rend="bold">Śaka 14[62], Śā[rvvari], śu. 15,</hi> the name of the month not being clear. The year corresponds to <hi rend="bold">1540-41 A.D.</hi></p>						

						</summary>
